    "translations": {
      "en": {
        "summary": "Hammad ibn Isa al-Juhani, a prominent companion of the Imams, recounts how he asked Imam Musa al-Kadhim (AS) to pray that he be blessed with a child and never be deprived of performing Hajj. The Imam's supplication was answered: Hammad was granted a son, and whenever the Hajj season came and he lacked funds, Allah provided from unexpected sources, echoing the Quranic promise in Surah al-Talaq (65:3).",
        "key_terms": {
          "فداك": "Ransom/sacrifice for you — an expression of deep reverence used when addressing the Imams",
          "الحج": "Hajj — the annual Islamic pilgrimage to Mecca",
          "النفقة": "Expenses/provisions — financial means needed for the journey",
          "أحتسب": "I reckon/expect — provision came without any expectation"
        },
        "seo_question": "What did Imam Musa al-Kadhim pray for Hammad ibn Isa regarding Hajj?"
